# Brand Design System

## Core Brand Colors (Three Anchors)

These are the three "true" brand colors. All other palette colors derive from gradients between them.

| Name | Hex | RGB | Usage |
|------|-----|-----|-------|
| **Amber** | `#F7821B` | `rgb(247, 130, 27)` | Energy, warmth, CTAs, highlights |
| **Rose** | `#E8497E` | `rgb(232, 73, 126)` | Accents, active states, alerts |
| **Sky** | `#5AC8FA` | `rgb(90, 200, 250)` | Trust, links, primary actions, calm |

## Gradient Intermediaries

Colors that naturally appear along the gradient edges between anchors:

| Name | Hex | Position |
|------|-----|----------|
| Coral | `#F06A42` | Amber → Rose (25%) |
| Watermelon | `#EC5660` | Amber → Rose (50%) |
| Magenta | `#D94E9A` | Rose → Sky (25%) |
| Lavender | `#A874C4` | Rose → Sky (50%) |
| Periwinkle | `#7A9EDF` | Rose → Sky (75%) |
| Gold | `#C9A332` | Amber → Sky (25%) |
| Seafoam | `#8AC486` | Amber → Sky (50%) |
| Aqua | `#6DCEC1` | Amber → Sky (75%) |

## Brand Gradients

Always use these predefined gradients — never invent new gradient combos.

```css
/* Full spectrum — hero sections, backgrounds, splashes */
--gradient-spectrum: linear-gradient(135deg, #F7821B 0%, #E8497E 50%, #5AC8FA 100%);

/* Warm — CTAs, buttons, badges */
--gradient-warm: linear-gradient(135deg, #F7821B 0%, #E8497E 100%);

/* Cool — cards, info panels, secondary actions */
--gradient-cool: linear-gradient(135deg, #E8497E 0%, #5AC8FA 100%);

/* Sunset — ambient backgrounds, decorative */
--gradient-sunset: linear-gradient(180deg, #F7821B 0%, #EC5660 50%, #5AC8FA 100%);

/* Radial — icon backgrounds, avatar rings, orbs */
--gradient-radial: radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%, #F7821B, #E8497E 50%, #5AC8FA 100%);

/* Mesh — full-bleed immersive backgrounds (use with multiple gradient layers) */
--gradient-mesh:
  radial-gradient(ellipse at 0% 0%, rgba(247,130,27,0.8) 0%, transparent 50%),
  radial-gradient(ellipse at 100% 0%, rgba(232,73,126,0.8) 0%, transparent 50%),
  radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 100%, rgba(90,200,250,0.8) 0%, transparent 50%);
```

## CSS Custom Properties

Define these at `:root`. All components must reference tokens — never hardcode hex values.

```css
:root {
  /* Brand anchors */
  --color-amber: #F7821B;
  --color-rose: #E8497E;
  --color-sky: #5AC8FA;

  /* Intermediaries */
  --color-coral: #F06A42;
  --color-watermelon: #EC5660;
  --color-magenta: #D94E9A;
  --color-lavender: #A874C4;
  --color-periwinkle: #7A9EDF;
  --color-aqua: #6DCEC1;

  /* Semantic tokens */
  --color-primary: var(--color-sky);
  --color-accent: var(--color-rose);
  --color-highlight: var(--color-amber);
  --color-destructive: var(--color-watermelon);

  /* Neutrals (for glass surfaces, text, borders) */
  --color-white: #FFFFFF;
  --color-gray-50: #F9FAFB;
  --color-gray-100: #F3F4F6;
  --color-gray-200: #E5E7EB;
  --color-gray-400: #9CA3AF;
  --color-gray-600: #4B5563;
  --color-gray-800: #1F2937;
  --color-gray-900: #111827;
  --color-black: #000000;
}
```

## Usage Rules

1. **Gradients for decoration, solids for interaction.** Buttons use a single brand color (with hover shift); hero areas and backgrounds use gradients.
2. **Never place brand-colored text on brand-colored backgrounds.** Use white or near-black text on gradient/colored surfaces.
3. **Glass surfaces tint with brand colors.** When a glass card sits over a gradient background, its `background` should pick up a faint brand tint: `rgba(247,130,27,0.06)` for warm areas, `rgba(90,200,250,0.06)` for cool areas.
4. **Gradient direction matters.** Warm colors (amber) sit top-left; cool colors (sky) sit bottom-right. This follows the natural light direction established by the brand.
5. **Accessibility.** All text on gradient or colored backgrounds must meet WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1 body, 3:1 large text). Use white (`#FFFFFF`) text on brand colors. Note: Sky (`#5AC8FA`) is light — use dark text (`--color-gray-900`) on sky-colored surfaces instead of white.
